The paper deals with the problem of promoting cooperation between artificial learners, which is a central topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The proposed approach involves learning how to create incentives for cooperation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the social implications of artificial learning agents, which relates to the field of social computing (cs.SI).
